# Renode run template for the fidelity benchmark.
# The runner substitutes @REPL@, @ELF@ and @OUT@ before invoking Renode.
# Uses Renode's own shipped STM32F103 platform so the comparison is honest:
# that platform has no RCC clock-gating model and maps a 256 MB SRAM, which is
# exactly why the clockbug and rambug firmwares false-pass on it.
using sysbus
mach create
machine LoadPlatformDescription @@REPL@
usart1 CreateFileBackend @@OUT@
sysbus LoadELF @@ELF@
emulation RunFor "0.2"
quit
